# Clients — {{ORG_NAME}}

_Current and recent clients. The relationships that pay the bills
and the relationships the agency stewards. Read by CoS on every
inbound; read by KB when evaluating IP alignment; read by BD when
qualifying new leads (so we don't pitch existing clients)._

_Derived from interview {{INTERVIEW_DATE}}. Update as the roster
evolves._

---

## Active clients

{{ACTIVE_CLIENTS}}

_(Each one: name, what we're doing for them, who the primary
contact is, what they're paying (rough — exact in CRM), what they
expect from us. Sensitive — agents don't quote dollar figures
outbound.)_

## Recently completed engagements

{{COMPLETED_ENGAGEMENTS}}

_(Last 6-12 months. Useful for case studies, references, and
knowing when a former client might come back.)_

## Long-standing relationships (not currently engaged)

{{DORMANT_RELATIONSHIPS}}

_(People we've worked with before who aren't current clients but
matter to the relationship map. BD knows not to "prospect" them as
strangers.)_

## Standing collaborators (not clients but adjacent)

{{COLLABORATORS}}

_(People + organizations the agency partners with — co-authors,
sub-contractors, referral sources, peer firms. Agents treat
inbound from these differently than cold contacts.)_

## Client communication preferences

{{CLIENT_COMM_PATTERNS}}

_(Per-client (or per-category-of-client) communication preferences.
"Acme always wants weekly Friday updates." "BigCo only wants
calls, never emails." Calibration data for outbound.)_

## Renewal / billing cadence

{{BILLING_CADENCE}}

_(When clients renew, when invoices go out, when retainers reset.
CoS uses this to surface "the Acme renewal is in 3 weeks; have we
done the planning meeting?")_

## Client-specific rules

{{CLIENT_SPECIFIC_RULES}}

_(Things the agency has committed to a specific client — exclusivity
clauses, content embargoes, scheduling rules, no-fly recipients,
etc. Hard rules; agents enforce them at the send-guard layer.)_

---

_This file is sensitive. It contains pricing context and
relationship signal that shouldn't leak. Audit checks
`clients-md-leak` rule — anything from here appearing in outbound
copy is a blocking finding._
